  <channel>
    <title>Competitive, Content, Raiding Server (work in progress)</title>
    <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&amp;message.id=16485</link>
    <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Smakpopy, the Original&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Content Raiding Server&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;« 06-01-2006 05:05 AM »&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The "Progression" server is a step in the right direction, but can not maintain a healthy competitive environment for raiders.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Here is a general plan for a fun, challanging, feasible, raiding server that just might have a longer lifespan:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Starting character begins in the "Original EQ" era. This means no Iksars, Vah Shir, Berzerkers, or Beastlords. All revamped zones are reverted back to original states, or as close as possible. Items that no longer drop such as Manastone and Rubicite Breastplate are back! Journeymans boots are dropping in Najena once again.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;With some new changes: now when you reach the doors to enter the fire giant area in solb or the ice giants in vox's lair you will find an npc or object that raids can use to trigger a "raid instance". Inside the instance the min level is 46 and max level is 52 and you will find the giants and other monsters in and around Vox or Nagafen.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;When your defeat the encounter for the first time your character recieves the message "the heat/chill from Nagafen's/Vox's passing permeates your soul, you feel the barriers to Fear, Hate, and Sky weaken", (or something to that effect). When you have killed either one you are locked out of that instance for 5 days. When you have killed both dragons you are now capable of entering Fear, Hate, and Sky planes.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The planes of Fear, Hate, and Sky are all instanced zones. The npc to generate the Fear instance is located near the fear portal, entering Fear is still done by using the portal, but only after your raid has selected the instance. Fear has 2 types of instances, the first one has level req of 46 max level of 55 and provides a flag when you kill cazic thule. The second Fear instance has no max level but provides no flags, purely for loot and for epic parts later on. Killing a golem in fear adds a parallel zone lockout timer of 3 days. So killing 2 golems would place 2 lockout timers on your instance window that would both end in 3 days (very similar to the lockouts in the current Plane of Time zones). Killing Cazic Thule in the first instance adds a parallel 7 day lockout timer and gives you a message "You have overcome your Fears, yet you still feel a deep Hatred toward all living things", (or something to that effect). The lockout timers from either type of instance will prevent you from entering both.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The plane of Hate has 3 instances, the npcs to trigger them stand on each of the wizard spires around "Original EQ" zones except for the one in the Temple of Cazic Thule. The first one has a min level of 46 max level of 55. Killing "Named Minis" give you a 3 day lockout timer. Killing Innorouk gives you a 7 day lockout timer and the message "You have overcome deep seated Hatreds, and conquered your Fears of the unknown, you have gained access to the Ruins of Kunark", (or something to that effect). The second instance has min level req of 46 and no max level but provides no flags, purely for loot and epic hunts. The 3rd instance of Hate is actually the revamped "HateB" and will not be available until your character has accessed the Planes of Power.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The plane of Sky has one instance, min level if 46 and no level cap. It is purely for loot, quests, and epics.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Now, this is where it gets interesting...&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;When your character has killed Cazic Thule and Innorouk you recieve an "Account Flag". This flag has mulitple effects. The most basic change is your ability to zone to all the unlocked kunark zones and trigger kunark raid instances. You still require keys to enter zones such as Sebilis, Howling Stones, and Veeshans Peak. You also can create new Iksar characters, and your level cap rises to 60th. You can also wear items you find in Kunark. As you begin hunting in Kunark you will notice every item that does not drop in "Original EQ" is stamped with the "Content Era" that it dropped in. (all items found on corpses in Kunark will clearly say "Kunark" under the stats). **IMPORTANT: Items stamped with Kunark can only be worn by players who have obtained "Account Flags" from killing Vox/Nag/CT/Inny**&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;This all raises many questions, and the first answer is that... when the first raider completes all 4 flags (Vox, Nag, CT, Inny) he not only gains entrance to Kunark, but the ability to wear all kunark items with ANY character on his account of any level, he also gives "Serverwide" zone access to everyone else with some exceptions.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Unflagged people (missing one of vox/nag/ct/inny flags) gain the following:&lt;BR&gt;1. Ability to enter basic zones of kunark.&lt;BR&gt;2. Ability to join flag raids to kill Trakanon, Venril Sathir, Sev/Gore/Tal.&lt;BR&gt;3. Group, gain experience to 50th level, loot items they win, and hang with their guildmates.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Unflagged (missing one of vox/nag/ct/inny flags) people do NOT:&lt;BR&gt;1. Get to make Iksars.&lt;BR&gt;2. Get to level past 50th.&lt;BR&gt;3. Get to wear items specifically from Kunark and beyond (until flagged).&lt;BR&gt;4. Get to trigger raid instances.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In Karnors vs prep room is an npc that allows you to trigger the Venril Sathir instances. The first instance is min 46 max level 60th. Killing him gives your account part of the account flag to reach Velious. The second instance is min 46 no max level and is purely for loot and quests.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In Dreadlands, Emerald Jungle, and Skyfire Mountains are npcs to trigger raid instances containing Gore, Sev, and Tal respectively. You must kill at least ONE of these 3 dragons to earn your account flag to velious. 2 versions of each, first one is min 46 max 60, second is min 46 no max level and the second one gives no flags.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In sebilis, down near the juggs doorway is a trigger to enter the trakanon instance. First instance is min 46 max 60th level and can drop ton pos staff. Second instance is min 61 with no max level and both instances drop the normal loots bps or robe, quest items, teeth for Veeshans Peak keys.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;When your character has complete the entire Veeshans Peak key, has killed Venril Sathir, and at least one of the 3 Sev/Tal/Gore, AND has vox/nag/ct/inny flags, you get an account flag allowing you to enter Velious zones.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;When you have velious flag you gain the ability to enter Velious zones and trigger raid instances. And to wear Velious era-stamped items.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Ok, everyone else on the server **that HAS been fully flagged for Kunark** now automatically gains:&lt;BR&gt;1. The ability to enter Velious zones.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;People flagged for Kunark (have Vox/Nag/CT/Inny flags) but not Velious do NOT gain the ability to:&lt;BR&gt;1. Trigger raid instances.&lt;BR&gt;2. Wear items stamped with Velious era (items that only drop in Velious or later expansions).&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The players who do NOT have full Kunark flags (do not have Vox/Nag/CT/Inny flags) CANNOT enter Velious OR wear Velious items OR join raid instances.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Instanced content in velious:&lt;BR&gt;1. Yelinak&lt;BR&gt;2. Tormax&lt;BR&gt;3. Dain&lt;BR&gt;4. Velketor&lt;BR&gt;5. Statue and Avatar of War&lt;BR&gt;6. all of Temple of Veeshan&lt;BR&gt;7. all of Sleepers Tomb (Sleeper asleep, level 46-60)&lt;BR&gt;8. all of Sleepers Tomb (Sleeper awake, level 61+)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Flags required to earn luclin account flag:&lt;BR&gt;1. kill Arrynar (sp, 7 day lockout)&lt;BR&gt;2. kill one of (Yelinak, Tormax, Dain, or Velketor -7 day lockouts)&lt;BR&gt;3. obtain Sleepers key&lt;BR&gt;4. kill Phara Dar (vp, 7 day lockout)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Same rules as before, new expansion. Fully flagged to Luclin you can:&lt;BR&gt;1. enter Luclin zones&lt;BR&gt;2. create Vah Shir&lt;BR&gt;3. create Beastlords&lt;BR&gt;4. trigger Luclin raid instances.&lt;BR&gt;5. wear Luclin items with any character.&lt;BR&gt;6. gain alternate advancement points.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;After the expansion has been entered, anyone fully flagged to velious can:&lt;BR&gt;1. enter Luclin zones.&lt;BR&gt;2. CANNOT wear Luclin items&lt;BR&gt;3. CANNOT gain alternate advancement points.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Instanced raids in Luclin:&lt;BR&gt;1. Vex Thall. (Aten Ha Ra 7 day lockout, all other named 3 day)&lt;BR&gt;2. Ssra temple. (Emp 7 day lockout, all other named 3 day)&lt;BR&gt;3. Seru (trigger in arx, 7 day lockout)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Flags required to enter the Planes of Power:&lt;BR&gt;1. Complete Epic 1.0&lt;BR&gt;2. kill Avatar of War (kael, 4 day lockout)&lt;BR&gt;3. kill Dozecar the Cursed (tov, 7 day lockout)&lt;BR&gt;4. kill Vulak Aerr (ntov-clear, 7 day lockout)&lt;BR&gt;5. obtain Vex Thall key&lt;BR&gt;6. obtain Arx key (seru) **must be obtained by at LEAST one person in your guild, or personally advance to step in earring quest just before arx key if you are unguilded**&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Once the first player gets flagged to Planes of Power it unlocks POK and the Bazaar to all players. Level cap moves up to 65th in planes of power, and new aa skills become available.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Planes of Power flagging, backflagging left intact with some additions:&lt;BR&gt;1. elemental planes flag gives "account flag" to access both ldon and loy content. (first person completing this also opens up ldon and loy content for EVERYONE else, and everyone else can automatically use LDoN and LoY era stamped items.)&lt;BR&gt;2. time flag is part of progression to Gates of Discord.&lt;BR&gt;3. every PoP flag raid is now instanced.&lt;BR&gt;4. all "raid encounters" such as gods no longer appear in the persistant zones.&lt;BR&gt;5. all single groupable and soloable "flag steps" continue to appear in persistant zones.&lt;BR&gt;6. you MUST be finish all Luclin tasks and be fully PoP enabled until you can finish ANY backflagging quests, this includes all the shortcuts including the tier 3 Time key that drops from named.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Flags required to enter Gates of Discord:&lt;BR&gt;1. Time flag (full or gimped - t3 keyed)&lt;BR&gt;2. kill Aten Ha Ra (Vex Thall)&lt;BR&gt;3. kill Lord Inquisitor Seru (Sanctus Seru - arx)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Flags required to enter Omens of War, Dragons of Norrath, Depths of Darkhollow, and Prophecy of Ro:&lt;BR&gt;1. kill Quarm (Time)&lt;BR&gt;2. obtain Qvic flag&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;All of those expansions become available, and level cap rises to 70th once you finish with Barxt/Ikkinz4 and Quarm! This is because of the varied content all players can enjoy in those zones, not just hardcore.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;But, to open the new, as of yet unnamed, expansion after Prophecy of ro you must:&lt;BR&gt;1. Complete epic 2.0&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Some notes and additions:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Paludal Caverns removed from the game on general principle, im kidding... ( or am i ? )&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;After Planes of Power has been first entered, revamped zones such as Mistmoore, Cazic Thule, Plane of Mischief, Paw, Hole would exist in 2 persistant zones each. With the original version left as it is (except for PoM), and click to enter zonelines placed near the entrances of the old zones:&lt;BR&gt;1. MM (druid rings near zoneline)&lt;BR&gt;2. CT (pillars near ramp to ct)&lt;BR&gt;3. Hole (pool near warrens)&lt;BR&gt;4. PoM (revamped entrance is in Great Divide, old ToV zoneline is changed to new PoM)&lt;BR&gt;5. Paw (spires near paw)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Reminder, all items that do not drop in an expansion you have access to or in Original EQ are not wearable until you reach that flag.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Reminder, you can enter any zone one expansion beyond your account flags. But you cannot trigger raid instances or gain level caps or aa's, skills associated with that expansion.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;When you create new characters, they all have same access to content as your main or retired character. Meaning you CAN twink your alts and pick up flagging where you left off. Character based zone/raid flags/keys are still required to enter those zones.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Once the first guild breaks into Planes of Power, all the items that "no longer drop" disappear to fall in line with normal servers. Such as Rubicite Bp, Manastone, J-boots(quest only now), Circlet of Shadow, Rod of Annihilations, you get the picture. Paw, MM, Hole, and CT remain as dual persistant zones. But old PoM zoneline in NToV becomes just another zoneline to new PoM. The Sleeper is NOT automatically woken, but if all 4 warders are killed together again...&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;NO character transfers to or from this server.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Once the first player finishes Luclin and becomes officially PoP flagged, this action unlocks the plane of knowledge and the bazaar for all players. The guild hall becomes available at the appropriate expansion in the same manner, for all players.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;On alts:&lt;BR&gt;1. You can create ONE special alternate character of any class or race you have currently unlocked, This character can be any level from 1 up to your mains level minus 10 levels (so a 60th main could have a free 50th alt). This means you CAN assist your lower content guildmates and friends with their flag quests or simply to exp and group for fun.&lt;BR&gt;2. This alt, as all of your characters, automatically gains the ability to wear any gear your main can as far as "era stamping" is concerned. This is because your "era" is an account flag not character flag.&lt;BR&gt;3. If your special alt becomes the same level as your main through grouping and exping, you have the option of designating it as your main character. Your previous character automatically becomes your "special alt"&lt;BR&gt;4. This allows a lot of freedom in exploring the classes of norrath, and if you chose to make a change its not going to cost you months to do it.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;On Persistant Subguilds/Channels:&lt;BR&gt;1. everyone that is part of an overlapping era with you is automatically a member of one of your subguilds.&lt;BR&gt;2. everyone in Original and Kunark era, everyone in Kunark and Velious era, everyone in Velious and Luclin era, everyone in Luclin and PoP era, everyone in in PoP and Gates era, and everyone in Gates and beyond era, each of these pairs is a combined subguild. (when i say everyone in Original and Kunark era, im referring to players who cannot yet trigger instances in Kunark but can zone there because the first guild has given them access to the zones, not level caps ect)&lt;BR&gt;3. "Mentor Chat" is the channel where everyones lowest-era is = to your highest. These are the players who are most likely capable of assisting you in your hardest flags.&lt;BR&gt;4. "Peer Chat" is the channel where everyone has the same finished flag set as you. This is likely the best spot to find exp groups.&lt;BR&gt;5. "Disciple chat" is the channel where everyone's highest-era is = to your lowest, and is the best place to find players you are most capable of assisting with flags.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Subguilds and pickup raids, bonuses for unguilded-guilded players:&lt;BR&gt;1. a raid composed of entirely UNGUILDED players that defeats a flag encounter such as nagafen or vox, AUTOMATICALLY generates 3X the normal drops. Whatever it drops it automatically drops 3 of whatever was randomly generated. For example, if you kill Nagafen and a Cloak of flame, a Treasure Hunters Satchel, and 2 Red Dragon Scales would have dropped: you instead will find THREE cof, THREE wt red bags, and SIX red scales.&lt;BR&gt;2. the 3X loot rule only applies to pre Luclin flag raids, and only instances where flags where 12 or more flags were won.&lt;BR&gt;3. GUILDED players automatically gain an increase of 10% coin every month earned from defeating monsters in groups of 3-6 players, up to a maximum of 50%! bonus plat/gold/silver/copper, and ONLY from autosplit coin.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Limited PVP, added ability for anyone to become PVP flagged on a limited scale as follows:&lt;BR&gt;1. You click one of these options: "Coward", "Soldier", or "Insane"&lt;BR&gt;2. in "Coward" mode you can attack and be attacked by anyone who is "Insane" and whose highest-era equals your lowest-era.&lt;BR&gt;3. in "Soldier" mode you can attack and be attacked by any in "Soldier" mode who match your era flags.&lt;BR&gt;4. in "Insane" mode you can attack and be attacked by anyone in "Coward" move, whose lowest-era is equal to your highest-era.&lt;BR&gt;5. activating any pvp mode prevents you from getting any beneficial spells, heals, ect, and you CANNOT change modes again for a min of 5 mins.&lt;BR&gt;6. deactivating pvp mode makes it impossible to change modes for a min of 5 mins, you cannot deactivate unless you havent been the target of an attack for the last 60 seconds.&lt;BR&gt;7. ***if you are in insane mode and soloing you get 30% more exp per kill solo***&lt;BR&gt;8. **if you are in Soldier mode you gain 10% more exp per kill solo**&lt;BR&gt;9. *if you are in Coward mode you gain 5% more exp per kill solo*&lt;BR&gt;10. if you die in PVP mode to a single players aggression a zonewide message appears humiliating you.&lt;BR&gt;11. if you die in PVP mode to multiple players' aggression a zonewide message humiliates your attackers AND prevents them from turning PVP mode off for 20 mins. (this 20 min timer resets if they get attacked in any PVP form)&lt;BR&gt;12. soloing a mob while in any PVP mode prevents you from leaving PVP mode for 5 min timer.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Constructive criticism:&lt;BR&gt;Caudyr &amp;lt; Invictvs &amp;gt; Bertox For initial motivation and assistance with vision of the perfect raiding server.&lt;BR&gt;Warfust &amp;lt; Invictvs &amp;gt; Bertox For unwittingly spuring my imagination to deal with his complaints and general rudeness in creative ways.&lt;BR&gt;Baccas &amp;lt; Enlightenment &amp;gt; Bertox&lt;BR&gt;Marmax for his whining about carebear camps, my primary motivation to introduce quick and painful pvp.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;!--   BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_editedby   --&gt;&lt;FONT face=verdana,arial,helvetica size=1&gt;&lt;I&gt;Last edited by smakpopy on 06-01-2006 at 05:19 PM&lt;/I&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
