    <item>
      <title>Re: Competitive, Content, Raiding Server (work in progress)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&amp;message.id=16659#M16659</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;"At that point, you've effectively removed the point of instancing. =p&amp;nbsp; The idea behind instancing is that every guild gets access to a mob regardless of whether other guilds have killed it recently."&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;It would still provide a cleaner score of who is better at not just killing the boss but also clearing to it.&amp;nbsp; In a standard zone a guild can sit back and follow the other guild in then gank the boss, or kill it after the first guild fails.&amp;nbsp; It also would reduce lag for the fight, instead of having 2-3 guilds hovering over the mob, you would have 2 or 3 seperate instances each running smoothly.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Also, after the first era or two&amp;nbsp;of content has been "conquered", they could revert the instances back to my original plan where lockouts are only generated on a raid by raid basis, instead of serverwide.&amp;nbsp; This would allow guild lagging behind more opportunities to catch up or at least stay within 2 expansions of the top guild.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;If you get what i mean,&amp;nbsp; Im sort of jumping around with these ideas since i may be about to alter one aspect of my plan.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
